<TITLE> BNP defers Sunday protests over Wazed's death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 9 (bdnews24.com)Main opposition BNP has adjourned its human-chain protests scheduled for Sunday at the death of the prime minister's husband Dr M A Wazed Miah. BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia asked the party secretary-general Khandaker Delwar Hossain on Saturday evening to postpone the countrywide protest programme, her press secretary Maruf Kamal Khan told bdnews24.com. The protests were to be held at all metropolitan cities, Upazila and district headquarters to as part of a series of protests spread over a month to protest power, water, and gas crises and 'worsening security'. The demands include a fair investigation into bloody BDR mutiny, an end to 'efforts to hide the real perpetrators of the carnage' and 'repression' on opposition supporters across the country. On 14 May, BNP will hold agitation programme in protest against deteriorating law and order situation at all metropolitan cities , upzila and district headquarters across the country. On Apr 23, Delwar declared the programmes at BNP chairperson's Gulshan office. On May 14, countrywide rallies and processions will protest the 'deteriorating law and order'. All metropolises, districts and Upazilas would mark May 19 to demand an end to the 'atrocities being committed at educational institutions and politicisation everywhere'. b
